President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Kansas and has ordered Federal assistance to support State and local recovery efforts after a severe winter storm that occurred from January 13 to January 16, 2017. The Federal funding will be available to State and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in the affected counties. The funding will also be available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Michael L. Parker has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.